cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with zero-shot recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel framework for learning data-dependent feature transforms, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper tests its approach on benchmark datasets, which implies that it could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
